other_tests.findings: The right ovary had been replaced by a unilocular cyst measuring 9.3 cm by 6.0 cm containing a brown purulent fluid and inflammatory exudate.
Appendix appeared generally inflamed but otherwise normal.
Cultures grew varying amounts of methicillin-sensitive Staphylococcus aureus; thorough cultures negated anaerobic, mycobacterial, and fungal infections.
